About 1,650 Telkom Staff Accept Redundancy Packages, Business Day Reports

-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 
2011-05-25T04:59:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/about-1-650-telkom-staff-accept-redundancy-packages-business-day-reports.html
About 1,650 staff at Telkom South
Africa Ltd., a majority state-owned telecommunications company,
accepted voluntary severance or early retirement packages,
Business Day reported, citing labor union Solidarity.  The packages were effective from April 1, with the company
receiving 1,800 applications for them, the Johannesburg-based
newspaper reported. About 300 employees were asked to continue
working for six months to transfer skills to other staff. Telkom
had 23,247 permanent staff in fiscal 2010, 1.2 percent fewer
than a year earlier, Business Day said, citing the companyâ€™s
annual report.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
